    <p><img src="http://drupaleasy.com/sites/drupaleasy.com/files/tutorial_intro.png" alt="X Marks the Spot sample map" /><br />
Mapping address data in Drupal can be confusing, if only because of the great number of contributed modules available that involve online maps. Picking the right module (or combination of modules) is challenging - especially for site builders who are new to mapping in Drupal. In this tutorial, we'll utilize the popular and well-supported <a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/geofield">Geofield</a> module as one of the key ingredients in the common task of entering address data and having it displayed on an interactive map.</p>
<p>This tutorial contains step-by-step instructions for accomplishing this task, as well as a screencast demonstrating all of the steps.</p>

